      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Mesh convergence study performed on the non-cannulated screw geometry using three systematically refined meshes (coarse ~180k elements, medium ~420k elements, fine ~950k elements). Richardson extrapolation yields a grid convergence index of 1.4% for stiffness QoI and 2.3% for yield force QoI; the medium mesh was selected for production runs, achieving level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
