      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Independent model reviews were conducted by two engineers not involved in model construction. A documented simulation plan was approved prior to execution. Boundary condition application and material property assignment were verified against the simulation plan by an independent reviewer. Achieved level 3 exceeds required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic material model for titanium alloy (Ti-6Al-4V) is well-established for sub-yield loading. Nonlinear contact with Coulomb friction captures screw-rod interface behavior. Geometric nonlinearity is included for large-displacement loading to 40 mm. Model form selection is justified by prior literature and confirmed by validation results across three QoIs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Material properties sourced from certified material test reports for the specific Ti-6Al-4V alloy batch. Geometric dimensions measured from CMM data on production parts. Interface friction coefficient estimated from tribological literature and varied in the UQ campaign. Input uncertainty distributions are documented and propagated via Monte Carlo sampling (n=2000)."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "N=11 production-representative constructs tested (6 at laboratory A, 5 at laboratory B). Screws and rods sourced from the same production lots as the FEA model geometry. Sample traceability documented via lot numbers and CMM inspection reports confirming dimensional conformance."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single ASTM F1717 loading condition (static compression-bending at 5 mm/min crosshead speed, room temperature). Only one test condition was evaluated; required level 3 demands at least two distinct loading conditions or environmental conditions. Achieved level 2 falls below required level 3 — this is the one identified gap in the credibility assessment, acknowledged in the decision record."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
