    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels. The single gap — Test conditions (achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) — is offset by the strong quantitative output comparison (E/uval < 1.96 for all three QoIs), the use of three independent FEA codes, and the two-laboratory experimental dataset. The UQ campaign, which included Monte Carlo propagation and Sobol sensitivity analysis, provides additional confidence that the dominant uncertainty drivers are understood and bounded. The assessment team concludes that the overall credibility evidence is sufficient to support a Medium assurance level acceptance decision for the non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending submission claim.",
